results.lead_paragraph: LENSES Camera fans can attend tonight's award presentations for outstanding work in the field at 8-o'clock, when the 1975, winners are honored by the Society of Photographers in Communications. The 30-year-old group of professionals is meeting in the McGraw-Hill auditorium, 1221 Avenue of the Americas (at 50th Street). The tab for outsiders is $5; for reservations, call 6616450. Seating is limited.

headline.main: Borman to Succeed Hall As Chief of Eastern Air; EASTERN CHIEF TO NARROW ROLE

results.snippet: Floyd D. Hall, chairman of Eastern Air Lines, announced yesterday that effective Dec. 16, following expiration of his 12-year employment contract, he would cease being chief executive officer but would continue as chairman.
